cyclomatic-complexity.description: TuringArena.settleRound(uint256) (contracts/TuringArena.sol#316-411) has a high cyclomatic complexity (19).
TuringArena._allocateRewards(uint256) (contracts/TuringArena.sol#573-629) has a high cyclomatic complexity (12).

divide-before-multiply.description:
TuringArena._allocateRewards(uint256) (contracts/TuringArena.sol#573-629) performs a multiplication on the result of a division:
	- rankingPool = (totalPrize * RANKING_SHARE) / BASIS_POINTS (contracts/TuringArena.sol#580)
	- rankReward = (rankingPool * RANKING_WEIGHTS[i]) / BASIS_POINTS (contracts/TuringArena.sol#598)

timestamp.description:
SessionKeyValidator.isSessionValid(address) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#61-65) uses timestamp for comparisons
	Dangerous comparisons:
	- (session.owner != address(0) && block.timestamp <= session.expiresAt && ! session.isRevoked && session.usageCount < session.maxUsage) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#63-64)

SessionKeyValidator.revokeSession(address) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#51-56) uses timestamp for comparisons
	Dangerous comparisons:
	- require(bool,string)(sessions[_sessionKey].owner == msg.sender,Not session owner) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#52)
	- require(bool,string)(! sessions[_sessionKey].isRevoked,Already revoked) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#53)

SessionKeyValidator.createSession(address,uint256,uint256) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#32-47) uses timestamp for comparisons
	Dangerous comparisons:
	- require(bool,string)(sessions[_sessionKey].owner == address(0),Session already exists) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#34)

SessionKeyValidator.getSessionRemainingTime(address) (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#70-74) uses timestamp for comparisons
	Dangerous comparisons:
	- block.timestamp >= session.expiresAt (contracts/security/SessionKeyValidator.sol#72)
